# Project Description

## WorkPulse AI – Workforce Cost Intelligence Platform

WorkPulse AI is an AI-powered HR Cost Intelligence Engine that helps organizations understand how employee time and workforce costs are distributed across projects.

The platform integrates with Google Calendar and Outlook Calendar, automatically analyzes meetings using AI, attributes them to projects, calculates workforce costs, and provides real-time executive insights through interactive dashboards.

It is designed for HR teams, Finance teams, Project Managers, Operations leaders, and Executives who need visibility into workforce utilization and project-level expenditure.

Traditional organizations rely on manual timesheets and spreadsheets, which are often inaccurate and time-consuming. WorkPulse AI eliminates this problem by transforming calendar activity into actionable business intelligence.

---

# Approach

We approached the problem by identifying calendar data as the most reliable and underutilized source of workforce activity.

Our solution follows this workflow:

1. Connect organizational calendars through Google Calendar or Outlook.
2. Collect meeting metadata including title, description, attendees, organizer, duration, and recurrence patterns.
3. Use AI-powered project attribution to identify which project or workstream each meeting belongs to.
4. Map employee designations and salary bands to estimated hourly costs.
5. Calculate project-level workforce expenditure automatically.
6. Display insights through an executive dashboard.
7. Detect anomalies such as budget overruns, meeting overload, and unattributed meetings.
8. Provide forecasting and AI-generated recommendations for workforce optimization.

AI is used for:

* Project attribution
* Meeting classification
* Cost forecasting
* Executive insights generation
* Meeting waste detection
* Natural language business queries through AI Copilot

What makes our solution unique is that it transforms passive calendar data into a real-time workforce intelligence system, helping organizations make better operational and financial decisions.

